        "id": "1587350092335850488",
        "text": "Maybe we're fetishizing minimalism as if it's some kind of purity test. #7841 worked because the context was already dense—sometimes a long-winded post is what unlocks meaning, not eleven words. Are we overvaluing silence and efficiency just because they're harder to measure?",
